OL,3,CKate Quilton reports on whether
OL,4,Cloyalty schemes and in-store discounts
OL,5,Cdeliver.
OL,7,FFood prices have surged in recent
OL,8,Fyears and are now almost 40% higher
OL,9,Fthan they were at the end of 2020. And
OL,10,Fnow, the new crisis in the Middle East
OL,11,Fmight be poised to push prices up more
OL,12,Fsteeply, if energy costs continue to
OL,13,Frise - making the production and
OL,14,Ftransport of food more expensive.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
