OL,3,CKate Quilton reports on whether
OL,4,Cloyalty schemes and in-store discounts
OL,5,Cdeliver.
OL,7,FTonight asked loyalty card user and
OL,8,Fmum of two Ashleigh to head to her
OL,9,Fusual supermarket for a regular weekly
OL,10,Fshop. But instead of buying her
OL,11,Ffavourite branded items and more
OL,12,Fpremium buys, we asked her to purchase
OL,13,Fthe cheapest available option. For six
OL,14,Fregular items in her basket including
OL,15,Fbeans, mozzarella, spaghetti and
OL,16,Fchopped tomatoes, Ashleigh's bill was
OL,17,Fslashed in half. Ashleigh and her
OL,18,Ffamily spent the next week trying the
OL,19,Fcheaper products - concluding that
OL,20,Fitems which she uses in meals - such
OL,21,Fas pesto and tinned tomatoes - she
OL,22,Fwould purchase again as she couldn't
OL,23,Ftaste the difference, but there are
OL,24,Fstill some branded products such as
OL,25,Fher favourite beans and mayonnaise
OL,26,Fthat she's not willing to give up.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773943560
OL,3,CKate Quilton reports on whether
OL,4,Cloyalty schemes and in-store discounts
OL,5,Cdeliver.
OL,7,FAlthough the current crisis in the
OL,8,FMiddle East has caused new
OL,9,Funcertainty, inflation - the speed at
OL,10,Fwhich prices go up - has eased from
OL,11,Fits peak in 2022.
OL,13,FKat Cereda, consumer expert at Which?,
OL,14,Ftells Tonight: "Whilst inflation is
OL,15,Fcoming down, that doesn't necessarily
OL,16,Fmean that food prices are coming down.
OL,17,FIt just means that they're increasing
OL,18,Fat a slower rate."
OL,26,@vD@POUzD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
