PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773943560
OL,3,CKate Quilton reports on whether
OL,4,Cloyalty schemes and in-store discounts
OL,5,Cdeliver.
OL,7,FBut as well as being commercially
OL,8,Fvaluable for supermarkets, researchers
OL,9,Fbelieve that data can be a goldmine in
OL,10,Fother ways too. Dr Anya Skatova,
OL,11,FAssociate Professor & Director at
OL,12,FDigital Footprints Lab at the
OL,13,FUniversity of Bristol, has been
OL,14,Flooking at how loyalty card data can
OL,15,Fhelp to improve public health. She
OL,16,Fexplained: "An important part of our
OL,17,Fresearch is to look at what people buy
OL,18,Ftogether in the same basket, and we
OL,19,Ffor example find in one study that in
OL,20,Fat least 25% of baskets, that 25% of
OL,21,Ftimes when people buy menstrual
OL,22,Fproducts they buy pain relief. This
OL,23,Fwill help us, for example, to set up
OL,24,Fmenstrual pain clinics in specific
OL,25,Fareas if we see a really high level of
OL,26,Fpurchases of certain products."
OL,26,@xD@LOUBE@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
